Super Talented Medical Writers needed in Hong Kong and Singapore!

Our client is a market leader in the pharmaceutical marketing and digital health solutions space. They provide clinical information, medical marketing and media services to the healthcare and pharmaceutical industries.
They have offices in all the major cities across APAC including Singapore, Australia, China, Hong Kong, India, Indonesia, Korea, Malaysia, Myanmar, New Zealand, Philippines, Singapore, Thailand, Vietnam and Japan.
We are recruiting for Senior/Lead Medical Writers for their 2 key Asia offices of Hong Kong and Singapore.

Reporting to the Country Editorial Leader, The Medical Writer is responsible for creating content for our client’s print, digital and event solutions that meet the medical communications objectives of their pharma and healthcare professional-partners

Specific responsibilities
Requirements:
• Graduate degree in the sciences (PhD, MSc); healthcare science degree a plus (MD, PharmD, BSc in nursing or allied profession)
• At least 3 years’ experience working for a healthcare communications agency
• Excellent written and verbal communication skills – this is assessed on application
• Ability to distill complex scientific concepts into clear, concise messages
• Strong working knowledge of Microsoft Office applications

How to Apply:
If you have considered relocating, please email a copy of your up to date CV to julise@idealhealthcare.biz so we can view your experience in more detail and assess the level of assistance we can provide. Due to high numbers of applications for international opportunities, only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.